# Cytochrome C Oxidase Subunit 1 (COX1)

COX1 is a mitochondrial protein involved in the electron transport chain and cellular respiration. It is highly conserved across species and commonly used in molecular evolution and DNA barcoding studies.

This protein sequence is useful for phylogenetic analysis, evolutionary biology research, comparative proteomics, and species identification workflows. It is frequently analyzed in bioinformatics and biodiversity studies.
